Tom,<br><br>
My comments were generally directed, and not at you specifically. My reference to drive by shootings was a comparison to how our society handles things, the Vietnam civilian casualty situation, in my opinion, being handled out of proportion when compared to the natural proclivities of our domestic state of affairs. We seem to be more tolerant of what we do to ourselves in &quot;peace&quot; than what happened in the unavoidable or extenuating circumstances of the Vietnam war.<br><br>
Compared to what goes on in the civilian sector, it seems that the Vietnam Soldier was a cut above the rest, even far above some of those who have tried to assign guilt in the way of propaganda. <br><br>

